data.value:
Word 2007 Demo
Essential Tools has come up with a new control ‘RibbonControlAdv’ which, allows users to experience the exact Office 2007 UI look and feel in their applications. All three office color schemes are supported. This sample demonstrates a sample Word application that is created using RibbonControlAdv along with Essential Tools controls such as Super Tooltip and Super Accelerator.
Ribbon Control Adv
The RibbonControlAdv is the main control which is at the top of the application. It has a MenuButton and a Quick Access Toolbar. Using the SmartTag, buttons for the Quick Access Toolbar and the Tab Items can easily be added.
Ribbon Form
The Office 2007 look and feel can be implemented for the form by inheriting from the RibbonForm class. Users are allowed to switch between the three office theme colors: blue, silver and black by setting a property. The top left corner of the ribbon form is curved in nature whose radius can be varied.
Quick Access Toolbar
RibbonControlAdv provides supports the QuickAccessToolbar. Users can add buttons to the QAT at design time by clicking the Add Quick Button from the Smart Tag. One can customize the Quick Access Toolbar by using the Customize Quick Access Toolbar Editor which, can be accessed by right clicking the dropdown arrow of the Quick Access Toolbar.
ToolStripTabItem
The ToolStripTabItem can be used to add tabs to the RibbonControlAdv. As many tabs can be added to the RibbonControlAdv. Each TabItem can contain a number of ToolStripEx which, will allow you to align the controls in groups inside the TabItem.
ToolStripEx
The ToolStripEx is an extension of ToolStrip. It allows the users to add all the controls that are supported by ToolStrip with Office 2007 look and feel. In addition, Syncfusion offers ToolStripPanelItem which, allows users to add any number of items with the specified Row Count.
Super Tooltip
Essential Tools provides support for Super Tooltip. It exhibits the exact look and feel of Screen Tips supported by the Office 2007 UI. Users are allowed to change the back color of the Super Tooltip for individual items. The Super Tooltip has three parts: Header, Body and Footer. Images can be associated with all three parts of it. Text alignment customization is also supported. The Super Tooltip can be set to display with the specified initial delay. The Super Tooltip can be used with .Net controls like a MenuStrip, ToolStrip and Syncfusion controls.
Super Accelerator
The Super Accelerator support is also provided by Essential Tools. The Accelerator keys provide an easy way to access the controls that are used in the application. When the Alt key is pressed, the corresponding accelerator keys will be displayed for the controls that are used in the application. The backcolor, forecolor and font of the accelerator can easily be customized.
